{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1252,"text":"Looking deeply inside nature,"},{"time":3982,"text":"through the magnifying glass of science,"},{"time":7095,"text":"designers extract principles,\nprocesses and materials"},{"time":10700,"text":"that are forming the very basis\nof design methodology."},{"time":15252,"text":"From synthetic constructs\nthat resemble biological materials,"},{"time":20352,"text":"to computational methods\nthat emulate neural processes,"},{"time":23743,"text":"nature is driving design."},{"time":27398,"text":"Design is also driving nature."},{"time":30128,"text":"In realms of genetics, regenerative\nmedicine and synthetic biology,"},{"time":33887,"text":"designers are growing novel technologies,"},{"time":36616,"text":"not foreseen or anticipated by nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41140,"text":"Bionics explores the interplay\nbetween biology and design."},{"time":47107,"text":"As you can see, my legs are bionic."},{"time":50990,"text":"Today, I will tell human stories\nof bionic integration;"},{"time":56538,"text":"how electromechanics attached\nto the body, and implanted inside the body"},{"time":62261,"text":"are beginning to bridge the gap\nbetween disability and ability,"},{"time":66999,"text":"between human limitation\nand human potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72681,"text":"Bionics has defined my physicality."},{"time":76228,"text":"In 1982, both of my legs were amputated"},{"time":78704,"text":"due to tissue damage from frostbite,"},{"time":80832,"text":"incurred during\na mountain-climbing accident."},{"time":83950,"text":"At that time, I didn't\nview my body as broken."},{"time":88417,"text":"I reasoned that a human being\ncan never be \"broken.\""},{"time":93655,"text":"Technology is broken."},{"time":96409,"text":"Technology is inadequate."},{"time":99638,"text":"This simple but powerful idea\nwas a call to arms,"},{"time":104120,"text":"to advance technology\nfor the elimination of my own disability,"},{"time":108651,"text":"and ultimately, the disability of others."},{"time":112460,"text":"I began by developing specialized limbs"},{"time":115442,"text":"that allowed me to return\nto the vertical world"},{"time":117927,"text":"of rock and ice climbing."},{"time":119418,"text":"I quickly realized that the artificial\npart of my body is malleable;"},{"time":124060,"text":"able to take on any form, any function --"},{"time":128434,"text":"a blank slate for which to create,"},{"time":131397,"text":"perhaps, structures that could extend\nbeyond biological capability."},{"time":137391,"text":"I made my height adjustable."},{"time":138765,"text":"I could be as short as five feet\nor as tall as I'd like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141469,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143922,"text":"So when I was feeling bad about myself,"},{"time":147296,"text":"insecure, I would jack my height up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149157,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151062,"text":"But when I was feeling\nconfident and suave,"},{"time":153283,"text":"I would knock my height down a notch,\njust to give the competition a chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157076,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159195,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161322,"text":"Narrow-edged feet allowed me\nto climb steep rock fissures,"},{"time":164615,"text":"where the human foot cannot penetrate,"},{"time":167241,"text":"and spiked feet enabled me\nto climb vertical ice walls,"},{"time":171447,"text":"without ever experiencing\nmuscle leg fatigue."},{"time":175399,"text":"Through technological innovation,"},{"time":177613,"text":"I returned to my sport,\nstronger and better."},{"time":180478,"text":"Technology had eliminated my disability,"},{"time":183085,"text":"and allowed me a new climbing prowess."},{"time":185451,"text":"As a young man, I imagined a future world\nwhere technology so advanced"},{"time":189038,"text":"could rid the world of disability,"},{"time":190844,"text":"a world in which neural\nimplants would allow"},{"time":192964,"text":"the visually impaired to see."},{"time":195026,"text":"A world in which the paralyzed\ncould walk, via body exoskeletons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200645,"text":"Sadly, because of\ndeficiencies in technology,"},{"time":203447,"text":"disability is rampant in the world."},{"time":205205,"text":"This gentleman is missing three limbs."},{"time":207903,"text":"As a testimony to current technology,\nhe is out of the wheelchair,"},{"time":211750,"text":"but we need to do a better job in bionics,\nto allow, one day, full rehabilitation"},{"time":217695,"text":"for a person with this level of injury."},{"time":221876,"text":"At the MIT Media Lab, we've established\nthe Center for Extreme Bionics."},{"time":225479,"text":"The mission of the center\nis to put forth fundamental science"},{"time":230051,"text":"and technological capability"},{"time":231911,"text":"that will allow the biomechatronic\nand regenerative repair of humans,"},{"time":235682,"text":"across a broad range\nof brain and body disabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241707,"text":"Today, I'm going to tell you\nhow my legs function, how they work,"},{"time":245468,"text":"as a case in point for this center."},{"time":248770,"text":"Now, I made sure to shave\nmy legs last night,"},{"time":250921,"text":"because I knew I'd be showing them off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252892,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254365,"text":"Bionics entails the engineering\nof extreme interfaces."},{"time":257619,"text":"There's three extreme\ninterfaces in my bionic limbs:"},{"time":260515,"text":"mechanical, how my limbs\nare attached to my biological body;"},{"time":264619,"text":"dynamic, how they move\nlike flesh and bone;"},{"time":267942,"text":"and electrical, how they communicate\nwith my nervous system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270856,"text":"I'll begin with mechanical interface."},{"time":273904,"text":"In the area of design,\nwe still do not understand"},{"time":277071,"text":"how to attach devices\nto the body mechanically."},{"time":281185,"text":"It's extraordinary to me\nthat in this day and age,"},{"time":284352,"text":"one of the most mature,\noldest technologies"},{"time":286701,"text":"in the human timeline, the shoe,\nstill gives us blisters."},{"time":291121,"text":"How can this be?"},{"time":292602,"text":"We have no idea how to attach\nthings to our bodies."},{"time":296364,"text":"This is the beautifully\nlyrical design work"},{"time":299293,"text":"of Professor Neri Oxman\nat the MIT Media Lab,"},{"time":301738,"text":"showing spatially varying\nexoskeletal impedances,"},{"time":305186,"text":"shown here by color variation\nin this 3D-printed model."},{"time":309811,"text":"Imagine a future where clothing\nis stiff and soft where you need it,"},{"time":314359,"text":"when you need it, for optimal\nsupport and flexibility,"},{"time":317913,"text":"without ever causing discomfort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320112,"text":"My bionic limbs are attached\nto my biological body"},{"time":323558,"text":"via synthetic skins\nwith stiffness variations,"},{"time":327644,"text":"that mirror my underlying\ntissue biomechanics."},{"time":332359,"text":"To achieve that mirroring, we first\ndeveloped a mathematical model"},{"time":335557,"text":"of my biological limb."},{"time":337129,"text":"To that end, we used\nimaging tools such as MRI,"},{"time":340435,"text":"to look inside my body,"},{"time":342023,"text":"to figure out the geometries\nand locations of various tissues."},{"time":345752,"text":"We also took robotic tools --"},{"time":347163,"text":"here's a 14-actuator circle\nthat goes around the biological limb."},{"time":352891,"text":"The actuators come in,\nfind the surface of the limb,"},{"time":355463,"text":"measure its unloaded shape,"},{"time":357732,"text":"and then they push on the tissues"},{"time":359407,"text":"to measure tissue compliances\nat each anatomical point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363542,"text":"We combine these imaging and robotic data"},{"time":365813,"text":"to build a mathematical description\nof my biological limb, shown on the left."},{"time":369479,"text":"You see a bunch of points, or nodes?"},{"time":371257,"text":"At each node, there's a color\nthat represents tissue compliance."},{"time":374431,"text":"We then do a mathematical transformation\nto the design of the synthetic skin,"},{"time":378397,"text":"shown on the right."},{"time":380088,"text":"And we've discovered optimality is:"},{"time":382516,"text":"where the body is stiff,\nthe synthetic skin should be soft,"},{"time":385397,"text":"where the body is soft,\nthe synthetic skin is stiff,"},{"time":388881,"text":"and this mirroring occurs\nacross all tissue compliances."},{"time":392720,"text":"With this framework,\nwe've produced bionic limbs"},{"time":395505,"text":"that are the most comfortable\nlimbs I've ever worn."},{"time":399077,"text":"Clearly, in the future, our clothing,\nour shoes, our braces, our prostheses,"},{"time":405190,"text":"will no longer be designed\nand manufactured using artisan strategies,"},{"time":408870,"text":"but rather, data-driven\nquantitative frameworks."},{"time":412098,"text":"In that future, our shoes\nwill no longer give us blisters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417040,"text":"We're also embedding\nsensing and smart materials"},{"time":419961,"text":"into the synthetic skins."},{"time":421556,"text":"This is a material developed\nby SRI International, California."},{"time":426048,"text":"Under electrostatic effect,\nit changes stiffness."},{"time":429349,"text":"So under zero voltage,\nthe material is compliant,"},{"time":432698,"text":"it's floppy like paper."},{"time":434096,"text":"Then the button's pushed,\na voltage is applied,"},{"time":436588,"text":"and it becomes stiff as a board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438604,"text":"(Tapping sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441666,"text":"We embed this material\ninto the synthetic skin"},{"time":444338,"text":"that attaches my bionic limb\nto my biological body."},{"time":447888,"text":"When I walk here, it's no voltage."},{"time":450342,"text":"My interface is soft and compliant."},{"time":452423,"text":"The button's pushed,\nvoltage is applied, and it stiffens,"},{"time":455438,"text":"offering me a greater maneuverability\nover the bionic limb."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458915,"text":"We're also building exoskeletons."},{"time":461327,"text":"This exoskeleton becomes stiff and soft"},{"time":463607,"text":"in just the right areas\nof the running cycle,"},{"time":466569,"text":"to protect the biological joints\nfrom high impacts and degradation."},{"time":470847,"text":"In the future, we'll all\nbe wearing exoskeletons"},{"time":473657,"text":"in common activities, such as running."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476966,"text":"Next, dynamic interface."},{"time":478474,"text":"How do my bionic limbs\nmove like flesh and bone?"},{"time":481799,"text":"At my MIT lab, we study how humans\nwith normal physiologies"},{"time":485808,"text":"stand, walk and run."},{"time":487338,"text":"What are the muscles doing,"},{"time":488753,"text":"and how are they controlled\nby the spinal cord?"},{"time":491697,"text":"This basic science\nmotivates what we build."},{"time":494166,"text":"We're building bionic ankles,\nknees and hips."},{"time":496528,"text":"We're building body parts\nfrom the ground up."},{"time":499854,"text":"The bionic limbs that I'm wearing\nare called BiOMs."},{"time":503041,"text":"They've been fitted\nto nearly 1,000 patients,"},{"time":507019,"text":"400 of which have been\nwounded U.S. soldiers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510005,"text":"How does it work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511187,"text":"At heel strike, under computer control,"},{"time":513226,"text":"the system controls stiffness,"},{"time":515226,"text":"to attenuate the shock\nof the limb hitting the ground."},{"time":518287,"text":"Then at mid-stance, the bionic limb\noutputs high torques and powers"},{"time":522407,"text":"to lift the person\ninto the walking stride,"},{"time":524786,"text":"comparable to how muscles\nwork in the calf region."},{"time":529096,"text":"This bionic propulsion is very important\nclinically to patients."},{"time":532850,"text":"So on the left, you see\nthe bionic device worn by a lady,"},{"time":535928,"text":"on the right, a passive device\nworn by the same lady,"},{"time":538887,"text":"that fails to emulate\nnormal muscle function,"},{"time":541737,"text":"enabling her to do something\neveryone should be able to do:"},{"time":545439,"text":"go up and down their steps at home."},{"time":547634,"text":"Bionics also allows\nfor extraordinary athletic feats."},{"time":551149,"text":"Here's a gentleman running\nup a rocky pathway."},{"time":555784,"text":"This is Steve Martin --\nnot the comedian --"},{"time":558633,"text":"who lost his legs in a bomb blast\nin Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562327,"text":"We're also building exoskeletal\nstructures using these same principles,"},{"time":567218,"text":"that wrap around the biological limb."},{"time":570311,"text":"This gentleman does not have\nany leg condition, any disability."},{"time":575922,"text":"He has a normal physiology,"},{"time":577826,"text":"so these exoskeletons are applying\nmuscle-like torques and powers,"},{"time":582419,"text":"so that his own muscles need not\napply those torques and powers."},{"time":587079,"text":"This is the first exoskeleton in history\nthat actually augments human walking."},{"time":592501,"text":"It significantly reduces metabolic cost."},{"time":595668,"text":"It's so profound in its augmentation,"},{"time":598406,"text":"that when a normal, healthy person\nwears the device for 40 minutes"},{"time":601579,"text":"and then takes it off,"},{"time":603302,"text":"their own biological legs feel\nridiculously heavy and awkward."},{"time":608039,"text":"We're beginning the age in which\nmachines attached to our bodies"},{"time":611474,"text":"will make us stronger\nand faster and more efficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615699,"text":"Moving on to electrical interface:"},{"time":617470,"text":"How do my bionic limbs communicate\nwith my nervous system?"},{"time":620651,"text":"Across my residual limb are electrodes"},{"time":622517,"text":"that measure the electrical\npulse of my muscles."},{"time":625286,"text":"That's communicated to the bionic limb,"},{"time":627229,"text":"so when I think about moving\nmy phantom limb,"},{"time":630306,"text":"the robot tracks those movement desires."},{"time":634020,"text":"This diagram shows fundamentally\nhow the bionic limb is controlled."},{"time":638670,"text":"So we model the missing biological limb,"},{"time":641099,"text":"and we've discovered\nwhat reflexes occurred,"},{"time":643937,"text":"how the reflexes of the spinal cord\nare controlling the muscles."},{"time":647302,"text":"And that capability is embedded\nin the chips of the bionic limb."},{"time":653009,"text":"What we've done, then, is we modulate\nthe sensitivity of the reflex,"},{"time":656993,"text":"the modeled spinal reflex,\nwith the neural signal,"},{"time":660112,"text":"so when I relax my muscles\nin my residual limb,"},{"time":663565,"text":"I get very little torque and power,"},{"time":666436,"text":"but the more I fire my muscles,\nthe more torque I get,"},{"time":669181,"text":"and I can even run."},{"time":672014,"text":"And that was the first demonstration\nof a running gait under neural command."},{"time":676982,"text":"Feels great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678158,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684149,"text":"We want to go a step further."},{"time":685558,"text":"We want to actually close the loop"},{"time":688629,"text":"between the human\nand the bionic external limb."},{"time":692407,"text":"We're doing experiments"},{"time":693582,"text":"where we're growing nerves,\ntransected nerves,"},{"time":696075,"text":"through channels, or micro-channel arrays."},{"time":698129,"text":"On the other side of the channel,"},{"time":699847,"text":"the nerve then attaches to cells,"},{"time":702200,"text":"skin cells and muscle cells."},{"time":704926,"text":"In the motor channels, we can sense\nhow the person wishes to move."},{"time":709070,"text":"That can be sent out wirelessly\nto the bionic limb,"},{"time":712731,"text":"then [sensory information]\non the bionic limb"},{"time":715137,"text":"can be converted to stimulations\nin adjacent channels,"},{"time":718662,"text":"sensory channels."},{"time":719918,"text":"So when this is fully developed\nand for human use,"},{"time":723970,"text":"persons like myself will not only have"},{"time":726630,"text":"synthetic limbs that move\nlike flesh and bone,"},{"time":730187,"text":"but actually feel like flesh and bone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734187,"text":"This video shows Lisa Mallette,"},{"time":736201,"text":"shortly after being fitted\nwith two bionic limbs."},{"time":739471,"text":"Indeed, bionics is making\na profound difference in people's lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742988,"text":"(Video) Lisa Mallette: Oh my God."},{"time":747519,"text":"LM: Oh my God, I can't believe it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":750678,"text":"(Video) (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":752145,"text":"LM: It's just like I've got a real leg!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757237,"text":"Woman: Now, don't start running."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758855,"text":"Man: Now turn around,\nand do the same thing walking up,"},{"time":761673,"text":"but get on your heel to toe, like you\nwould normally just walk on level ground."},{"time":765426,"text":"Try to walk right up the hill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769411,"text":"LM: Oh my God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772037,"text":"Man: Is it pushing you up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":773307,"text":"LM: Yes! I'm not even --\nI can't even describe it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778286,"text":"Man: It's pushing you right up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780608,"text":"Hugh Herr: Next week,\nI'm visiting the Center --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783180,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784356,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":787886,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789193,"text":"Next week I'm visiting the Center\nfor Medicare and Medicaid Services,"},{"time":793042,"text":"and I'm going to try to convince CMS"},{"time":795669,"text":"to grant appropriate\ncode language and pricing,"},{"time":798248,"text":"so this technology can be made available\nto the patients that need it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802003,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":803050,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804234,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807873,"text":"It's not well appreciated,\nbut over half of the world's population"},{"time":811841,"text":"suffers from some form of cognitive,\nemotional, sensory or motor condition,"},{"time":816632,"text":"and because of poor technology,\ntoo often, conditions result in disability"},{"time":821066,"text":"and a poorer quality of life."},{"time":823113,"text":"Basic levels of physiological function\nshould be a part of our human rights."},{"time":828077,"text":"Every person should have the right\nto live life without disability"},{"time":832057,"text":"if they so choose --"},{"time":833978,"text":"the right to live life\nwithout severe depression;"},{"time":836724,"text":"the right to see a loved one,\nin the case of seeing-impaired;"},{"time":840129,"text":"or the right to walk or to dance,"},{"time":842042,"text":"in the case of limb paralysis\nor limb amputation."},{"time":845633,"text":"As a society, we can\nachieve these human rights,"},{"time":849323,"text":"if we accept the proposition\nthat humans are not disabled."},{"time":855794,"text":"A person can never be broken."},{"time":858500,"text":"Our built environment, our technologies,"},{"time":861199,"text":"are broken and disabled."},{"time":863444,"text":"We the people need not\naccept our limitations,"},{"time":866500,"text":"but can transcend disability\nthrough technological innovation."},{"time":870599,"text":"Indeed, through fundamental advances\nin bionics in this century,"},{"time":874583,"text":"we will set the technological foundation\nfor an enhanced human experience,"},{"time":878765,"text":"and we will end disability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881456,"text":"I'd like to finish up\nwith one more story, a beautiful story."},{"time":885613,"text":"The story of Adrianne Haslet-Davis."},{"time":888360,"text":"Adrianne lost her left leg\nin the Boston terrorist attack."},{"time":892766,"text":"I met Adrianne when this photo was taken,\nat Spaulding Rehabilitation Hospital."},{"time":896745,"text":"Adrianne is a dancer, a ballroom dancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899245,"text":"Adrianne breathes and lives dance."},{"time":902366,"text":"It is her expression. It is her art form."},{"time":904660,"text":"Naturally, when she lost her limb\nin the Boston terrorist attack,"},{"time":908683,"text":"she wanted to return to the dance floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911828,"text":"After meeting her\nand driving home in my car,"},{"time":914011,"text":"I thought, I'm an MIT professor.\nI have resources."},{"time":917888,"text":"Let's build her a bionic limb,"},{"time":919450,"text":"to enable her to go back\nto her life of dance."},{"time":923396,"text":"I brought in MIT scientists\nwith expertise in prosthetics,"},{"time":926896,"text":"robotics, machine learning\nand biomechanics,"},{"time":929229,"text":"and over a 200-day research period,\nwe studied dance."},{"time":933389,"text":"We brought in dancers\nwith biological limbs,"},{"time":937310,"text":"and we studied how they move,"},{"time":939969,"text":"what forces they apply on the dance floor,"},{"time":943166,"text":"and we took those data,"},{"time":944717,"text":"and we put forth\nfundamental principles of dance,"},{"time":948516,"text":"reflexive dance capability,"},{"time":950327,"text":"and we embedded that intelligence\ninto the bionic limb."},{"time":953992,"text":"Bionics is not only about making\npeople stronger and faster."},{"time":957761,"text":"Our expression, our humanity\ncan be embedded into electromechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963520,"text":"It was 3.5 seconds between the bomb blasts\nin the Boston terrorist attack."},{"time":969733,"text":"In 3.5 seconds, the criminals and cowards\ntook Adrianne off the dance floor."},{"time":975860,"text":"In 200 days, we put her back."},{"time":978495,"text":"We will not be intimidated, brought down,\ndiminished, conquered or stopped"},{"time":983492,"text":"by acts of violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985061,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993046,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, please allow me\nto introduce Adrianne Haslet-Davis,"},{"time":997372,"text":"her first performance since the attack."},{"time":1000380,"text":"She's dancing with Christian Lightner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002541,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013579,"text":"(Music: \"Ring My Bell\"\nperformed by Enrique Iglesias)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059267,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1090170,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,\nmembers of the research team:"},{"time":1092962,"text":"Elliott Rouse"},{"time":1094981,"text":"and Nathan Villagaray-Carski."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097776,"text":"Elliott and Nathan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100187,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}